Job Title: Spring and Kafka Developer

Job Description:

We are seeking a talented and experienced Spring and Kafka Developer to join our dynamic and innovative development team. As a key member of the team, you will play a crucial role in designing, implementing, and maintaining scalable and high-performance systems that leverage the Spring framework and Kafka messaging platform.

Responsibilities:

    System Design and Architecture:
        Collaborate with cross-functional teams to design and architect robust and scalable systems using the Spring framework and Kafka.
        Develop and maintain a deep understanding of system architecture and how it aligns with business objectives.

    Spring Framework Development:
        Design, develop, and maintain Java applications using the Spring framework.
        Implement and optimize RESTful APIs to facilitate seamless integration with other systems.

    Kafka Integration:
        Design and implement Kafka-based solutions for real-time data streaming and event-driven architectures.
        Ensure reliable and efficient communication between distributed systems using Kafka messaging.

    Microservices Development:
        Contribute to the development of microservices-based applications, ensuring modularity, scalability, and maintainability.
        Implement best practices for containerization and orchestration of microservices using technologies like Docker and Kubernetes.

    Collaboration and Communication:
        Work closely with cross-functional teams, including front-end developers, DevOps engineers, and product owners, to deliver high-quality software solutions.
        Participate in code reviews and provide constructive feedback to team members.

    Performance Optimization:
        Identify and address performance bottlenecks in the system, ensuring optimal performance under varying workloads.

    Monitoring and Troubleshooting:
        Implement effective monitoring solutions for applications and Kafka clusters.
        Diagnose and resolve issues, ensuring the overall reliability of the systems.

Qualifications:

    Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.
    Proven experience as a Java developer with a strong focus on the Spring framework.
    Hands-on experience with Kafka, including the design and implementation of Kafka-based solutions.
    Experience in building and maintaining microservices architectures.
    Proficient in database design and optimization.
    Familiarity with containerization and orchestration technologies (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes).
    Strong problem-solving and debugging skills.
    Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
    Ability to adapt to a fast-paced and collaborative development environment.

Preferred Skills:

    Spring Boot, Spring Cloud experience.
    Knowledge of event sourcing and CQRS patterns.
    Familiarity with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP).
    Experience with CI/CD pipelines.

If you are a passionate developer with expertise in Spring and Kafka, and you are excited about contributing to cutting-edge projects, we encourage you to apply and become a valuable member of our forward-thinking development team.
